==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|'kwôrəl}}, {{IPA|/ˈkwɒrəl/}}, {{SAMPA|/"kwQr@l/}}
*: {{rhymes|ɒrəl}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} ''[[quarel]]'' (modern: ''[[querelle]]''), from {{VL.}} ''*quadrellus'' (diminutive of ''[[quadrus]]'' "square").

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
{{wikipedia}}

# A verbal [[dispute]] or heated [[argument]].
#: '''''Quarrels''' would not last long if the fault were only on one side'' - [[q:François de La Rochefoucauld|François de La Rochefoucauld]]
# A diamond-shaped piece of coloured [[glass]] forming part of a stained glass window.
# A square [[tile]]; [[quarry tile]] (from Old French quarrel or carreau;  Latin quadrellus, from quadrus - a square)
# A square-headed [[arrow]] for a [[crossbow]].

